48. Ibid., p. 254.

49. _1984 CBS Annual Report_, p. 13. This is a further refinement in the
measurement of “efficiency” in “delivering an audience.” In the magazine
business, the standard measure is CPM, or “costs per thousand,” to an
advertiser to reach buyers through a full-page, black-and-white ad.
Recent developments, like CBS’s CAP, have been in the direction of
identifying the special characteristics of the audience delivered. In
selling itself to advertisers, the _Soap Opera Digest_ says: “But you
probably want to know about our first milestone: today _Soap Opera
Digest_ delivers more women in the 18–49 category at the lowest CPM than
any other women’s magazine” (quoted in Turow, _Media Industries_, p.
55).

