provincial of the Jesuit order in Central America, Father César Jerez,
was called to Rome shortly after to explain the Romero letter. Father
Jerez, who had fled from Guatemala after the military had threatened his
life, was very close to Archbishop Romero. Subsequently he was forced to
flee El Salvador as well and is now a refugee in Nicaragua, where he is
rector of the Universidad Centroamericana, unable to return to the two
“fledgling democracies” except for brief (and dangerous) visits.

