Accused of Cover-up of Murder of Four American Women.” Santivánez was
paid $50,000 to give his evidence, a sum he requested on the ground of
the risk he was taking and the probability that he would be income-short
in the future as a result of his confession. This payment was given
unusual publicity as suggesting a compromising quality to his testimony,
and the _New York Times_ squelched a second installment of his evidence
on this principled ground—which they never apply to Soviet defectors,
who are less in need of protection. The revelation that the “leading
democrats” who were formed into a civilian front for the contras by the
CIA have been receiving over $80,000, tax-free, annually from the CIA
for years has never compromised their integrity as media sources.
Nicaraguan defector Miranda got $800,000 for his services without being
discredited.

