nowhere discusses Duarte’s and D’Aubuisson’s views on a negotiated
settlement of the war, which allows him to convey the erroneous
impression that one of them supported a nonmilitary route to ending the
violence and civil war _(El Salvador in Transition_ [Chapel Hill:
University of North Carolina Press, 1982], p. 175).

