43. The comprehensiveness of the _Times’s_ protection of its
disinformation sources was shown amusingly in February 1987 when Charles
Babcock, of the _Washington Post_, revealed that Ledeen had very
possibly been dismissed from Washington University in St. Louis in 1972
for plagiarism. On the very same day, an article by Stephen Engelberg in
the _Times_, on Ledeen, describes Ledeen’s history as follows: “After
being denied tenure at Washington University in St. Louis in 1972, Mr.
Ledeen became.…” This was all the news fit to print about a useful
asset.

