the southern part of the country, in a context where U.S. officials
readily admitted that the great majority of South Vietnamese supported
Ho Chi Minh and that Diem lacked an indigenous base of support.

38. We saw in chapter 3 that in El Salvador, too, while it was admitted
by the media that the population wanted peace above all else, the
